@node Improved Feint Combat
@section Improved Feint (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-feint-combat}
You are skilled at fooling your opponents in combat.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Int] 13, [Combat Expertise].

@strong{Benefit:} You can make a Bluff check to feint in combat as a move action.

@strong{Normal:} Feinting in combat is a standard action.

@node Improved Grapple Combat
@section Improved Grapple (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-grapple-combat}
You are skilled at grappling opponents.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Dex] 13, [Improved Unarmed Strike].

@strong{Benefit:} You do not provoke an attack of opportunity when performing a [grapple] combat maneuver. In addition, you receive a +2 bonus on checks made to [grapple] a foe. You also receive a +2 bonus to your [Combat Maneuver Defense] whenever an opponent tries to [grapple] you.

@strong{Normal:} You provoke an attack of opportunity when performing a [grapple] combat maneuver.

@node Improved Great Fortitude
@section Improved Great Fortitude
@anchor{#improved-great-fortitude}
You can draw upon an inner reserve to resist diseases, poisons, and other grievous harm.

@strong{Prerequisites:} @ref{#great-fortitude,Great Fortitude}.

@strong{Benefit:} Once per day, you may reroll a [Fortitude] save. You must decide to use this ability before the results are revealed. You must take the second roll, even if it is worse.

@node Improved Initiative Combat
@section Improved Initiative (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-initiative-combat}
Your quick reflexes allow you to react rapidly to danger.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +4 bonus on initiative checks.

@node Improved Iron Will
@section Improved Iron Will
@anchor{#improved-iron-will}
Your clarity of thought allows you to resist mental attacks.

@strong{Prerequisites:} @ref{#iron-will,Iron Will}.

@strong{Benefit:} Once per day, you may reroll a [Will] save. You must decide to use this ability before the results are revealed. You must take the second roll, even if it is worse.

@node Improved Lightning Reflexes
@section Improved Lightning Reflexes
@anchor{#improved-lightning-reflexes}
You have a knack for avoiding danger all around you.

@strong{Prerequisites:} @ref{#lightning-reflexes,Lightning Reflexes}.

@strong{Benefit:} Once per day, you may reroll a [Reflex] save. You must decide to use this ability before the results are revealed. You must take the second roll, even if it is worse.

@node Improved Overrun Combat
@section Improved Overrun (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-overrun-combat}
You are skilled at running down your foes.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Str] 13, [Power Attack], base attack bonus +1.

@strong{Benefit:} You do not provoke an attack of opportunity when performing an [overrun] combat maneuver. In addition, you receive a +2 bonus on checks made to overrrun a foe. You also receive a +2 bonus to your [Combat Maneuver Defense] whenever an opponent tries to [overrun] you. Targets of your [overrun] attempt may not chose to avoid you.

@strong{Normal:} You provoke an attack of opportunity when performing an [overrun] combat maneuver.

@node Improved Precise Shot Combat
@section Improved Precise Shot (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-precise-shot-combat}
Your ranged attacks ignore anything but total concealment and cover.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 19, [Point-Blank Shot], [Precise Shot], base attack bonus +11.

@strong{Benefit:} Your ranged attacks ignore the [AC] bonus granted to targets by anything less than total cover, and the miss chance granted to targets by anything less than total concealment. Total cover and total concealment provide their normal benefits against your ranged attacks.

@strong{Normal:} See the normal rules on the effects of cover and concealment in [Combat].

@node Improved Shield Bash Combat
@section Improved Shield Bash (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-shield-bash-combat}
You can protect yourself with your shield, even if you use it to attack.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Shield Proficiency].

@strong{Benefit:} When you perform a shield bash, you may still apply the shield's shield bonus to your [AC].

@strong{Normal:} Without this feat, a character that performs a shield bash loses the shield's shield bonus to [AC] until his next turn (see [Equipment]).

@node Improved Sunder Combat
@section Improved Sunder (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-sunder-combat}
You are skilled at damaging your foes' weapons and armor.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Str] 13, [Power Attack], base attack bonus +1.

@strong{Benefit:} You do not provoke an attack of opportunity when performing a [sunder] combat maneuver. In addition, you receive a +2 bonus on checks made to [sunder] an item. You also receive a +2 bonus to your [Combat Maneuver Defense] whenever an opponent tries to [sunder] your gear.

@strong{Normal:} You provoke an attack of opportunity when performing a [sunder] combat maneuver.

@node Improved Trip Combat
@section Improved Trip (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-trip-combat}
You are skilled at sending your opponents to the ground.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Int] 13, [Combat Expertise].

@strong{Benefit:} You do not provoke an attack of opportunity when performing a [trip] combat maneuver. In addition, you receive a +2 bonus on checks made to [trip] a foe. You also receive a +2 bonus to your [Combat Maneuver Defense] whenever an opponent tries to [trip] you.

@strong{Normal:} You provoke an attack of opportunity when performing a [trip] combat maneuver.

@node Improved Two-Weapon Fighting Combat
@section Improved Two-Weapon Fighting (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-two-weapon-fighting-combat}
@{#improved-two-weapon-fighting@}

You are skilled at fighting with two weapons.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 17, @ref{#two-weapon-fighting,Two-Weapon Fighting}, base attack bonus +6.

@strong{Benefit:} In addition to the standard single extra attack you get with an off-hand weapon, you get a second attack with it, albeit at a --5 penalty.

@strong{Normal:} Without this feat, you can only get a single extra attack with an off-hand weapon.

@node Improved Unarmed Strike Combat
@section Improved Unarmed Strike (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-unarmed-strike-combat}
You are skilled at fighting while unarmed.

@strong{Benefit:} You are considered to be armed even when unarmed---you do not provoke attacks of opportunity when you attack foes while unarmed. Your unarmed strikes can deal lethal or nonlethal damage, at your choice.

@strong{Normal:} Without this feat, you are considered unarmed when attacking with an unarmed strike, and you can deal only nonlethal damage with such an attack.

@node Improved Vital Strike Combat
@section Improved Vital Strike (Combat)
@anchor{#improved-vital-strike-combat}
You can make a single attack that deals a large amount of damage.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Vital Strike], base attack bonus +11.

@strong{Benefit:} When you use the attack action, you can make one attack at your highest base attack bonus that deals additional damage. Roll the weapon's damage dice for the attack three times and add the results together before adding bonuses from Strength, weapon abilities (such as [@emph{flaming}]), precision based damage, and other damage bonuses. These extra weapon damage dice are not multiplied on a critical hit, but are added to the total.

@node Improvised Weapon Mastery Combat
@section Improvised Weapon Mastery (Combat)
@anchor{#improvised-weapon-mastery-combat}
@{#improvised-weapon-mastery@}

You can turn nearly any object into a deadly weapon, from a razor-sharp chair leg to a sack of flour.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Catch Off-Guard] or [Throw Anything], base attack bonus +8.

@strong{Benefit:} You do not suffer any penalties for using an improvised weapon. Increase the amount of damage dealt by the improvised weapon by one step (for example, 1d4 becomes 1d6) to a maximum of 1d8 (2d6 if the improvised weapon is two-handed). The improvised weapon has a critical threat range of 19--20, with a critical multiplier of ×2.

@node Intimidating Prowess Combat
@section Intimidating Prowess (Combat)
@anchor{#intimidating-prowess-combat}
Your physical might is intimidating to others.

@strong{Benefit:} Add your Strength modifier to @ref{#intimidate,Intimidate} skill checks in addition to your [Charisma] modifier.

@node Iron Will
@section Iron Will
@anchor{#iron-will}
You are more resistant to mental effects.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +2 bonus on all [Will] saving throws.

