@* Followers have different priorities from cohorts. When you try to attract a follower, use the following modifiers.

@* The Leader... Modifier -------------------------------------------------------- ---------- Has a stronghold, base of operations, guildhouse, etc. +2 Moves around a lot --1 Caused the death of other followers --1

@* @emph{Leadership Score}: Your base Leadership score equals your level plus your [Charisma] modifier. In order to take into account negative [Charisma] modifiers, this table allows for very low Leadership scores, but you must still be 7th level or higher in order to gain the Leadership feat. Outside factors can affect your Leadership score, as detailed above.

@emph{Cohort Level}: You can attract a cohort of up to this level. Regardless of your Leadership score, you can only recruit a cohort who is two or more levels lower than yourself. The cohort should be equipped with gear appropriate for its level (see @ref{#creating-npcs,Creating NPCs}). A cohort can be of any race or class. The cohort's alignment may not be opposed to your alignment on either the law/chaos or good/evil axis, and you take a --1 penalty to your Leadership score if you recruit a cohort of an alignment different from your own.@* A cohort does not count as a party member when determining the party's XP. Instead, divide the cohort's level by your level. Multiply this result by the total XP awarded to you, then add that number of experience points to the cohort's total.

If a cohort gains enough XP to bring it to a level one lower than your level, the cohort does not gain the new level---its new XP total is 1 less than the amount needed to attain the next level.

@emph{Number of Followers by Level}: You can lead up to the indicated number of characters of each level. Followers are similar to cohorts, except they're generally low-level NPCs. Because they're usually 5 or more levels behind you, they're rarely effective in combat.

Followers don't earn experience and thus don't gain levels. When you gain a new level, consult Table: Leadership to determine if you acquire more followers, some of whom may be higher level than the existing followers. Don't consult the table to see if your cohort gains levels, however, because cohorts earn experience on their own.

@node Lightning Reflexes
@section Lightning Reflexes
@anchor{#lightning-reflexes}
You have faster reflexes than normal.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +2 bonus on all [Reflex] saving throws.

@node Lightning Stance Combat
@section Lightning Stance (Combat)
@anchor{#lightning-stance-combat}
The speed at which you move makes it nearly impossible for opponents to strike you.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 17, [Dodge], [Wind Stance], base attack bonus +11.

@strong{Benefit:} If you take two actions to move or a withdraw action in a turn, you gain 50% concealment for 1 round.

@node Lunge Combat
@section Lunge (Combat)
@anchor{#lunge-combat}
You can strike foes that would normally be out of reach.

@strong{Prerequisites:} Base attack bonus +6.

@strong{Benefit:} You can increase the reach of your melee attacks by 5 feet until the end of your turn by taking a --2 penalty to your [AC] until your next turn. You must decide to use this ability before any attacks are made.

@node Magical Aptitude
@section Magical Aptitude
@anchor{#magical-aptitude}
You are skilled at spellcasting and using magic items.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +2 bonus on all @ref{#spellcraft,Spellcraft} checks and @ref{#use-magic-device,Use Magic Device} checks. If you have 10 or more ranks in one of these skills, the bonus increases to +4 for that skill.

@node Manyshot Combat
@section Manyshot (Combat)
@anchor{#manyshot-combat}
You can fire multiple arrows at a single target.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 17, [Point-Blank Shot], [Rapid Shot], base attack bonus +6.

@strong{Benefit:} When making a full-attack action with a bow, your first attack fires two arrows. If the attack hits, both arrows hit. Apply precision-based damage (such as sneak attack) and critical hit damage only once for this attack. Damage bonuses from using a composite bow with a high Strength bonus apply to each arrow, as do other damage bonuses, such as a ranger's favored enemy bonus. Damage reduction and resistances apply separately to each arrow.

@node Martial Weapon Proficiency Combat
@section Martial Weapon Proficiency (Combat)
@anchor{#martial-weapon-proficiency-combat}
@{#martial-weapon-proficiency@}

Choose a type of martial weapon. You understand how to use that type of martial weapon in combat.

@strong{Benefit:} You make attack rolls with the selected weapon normally (without the non-proficient penalty).

@strong{Normal:} When using a weapon with which you are not proficient, you take a --4 penalty on attack rolls.

@strong{Special:} Barbarians, fighters, paladins, and rangers are proficient with all martial weapons. They need not select this feat.

You can gain Martial Weapon Proficiency multiple times. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new type of weapon.

@node Master Craftsman
@section Master Craftsman
@anchor{#master-craftsman}
Your superior crafting skills allow you to create simple magic items.

@strong{Prerequisites:} 5 ranks in any @ref{#craft,Craft} or @ref{#profession,Profession} skill.

@strong{Benefit:} Choose one @ref{#craft,Craft} or @ref{#profession,Profession} skill in which you possess at least 5 ranks. You receive a +2 bonus on your chosen @ref{#craft,Craft} or @ref{#profession,Profession} skill. Ranks in your chosen skill count as your caster level for the purposes of qualifying for the [Craft Magic Arms and Armor] and [Craft Wondrous Item] feats. You can create magic items using these feats, substituting your ranks in the chosen skill for your total caster level. You must use the chosen skill for the check to create the item. The DC to create the item still increases for any necessary spell requirements (see the magic item creation rules in [Magic Items]). You cannot use this feat to create any spell-trigger or spell-activation item.

@strong{Normal:} Only spellcasters can qualify for the [Craft Magic Arms and Armor] and [Craft Wondrous Item] feats.

@node Maximize Spell Metamagic
@section Maximize Spell (Metamagic)
@anchor{#maximize-spell-metamagic}
Your spells have the maximum possible effect.

@strong{Benefit:} All variable, numeric effects of a spell modified by this feat are maximized. Saving throws and opposed rolls are not affected, nor are spells without random variables. A maximized spell uses up a spell slot three levels higher than the spell's actual level.

An empowered, maximized spell gains the separate benefits of each feat: the maximum result plus half the normally rolled result.

@node Medusa's Wrath Combat
@section Medusa's Wrath (Combat)
@anchor{#medusas-wrath-combat}
You can take advantage of your opponent's confusion, delivering multiple blows.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Improved Unarmed Strike], [Gorgon's Fist], [Scorpion Style], base attack bonus +11.

@strong{Benefit:} Whenever you use the full-attack action and make at least one unarmed strike, you can make two additional unarmed strikes at your highest base attack bonus. These bonus attacks must be made against a [dazed], [flat-footed], [paralyzed], [staggered], [stunned], or [unconscious] foe.

@node Mobility Combat
@section Mobility (Combat)
@anchor{#mobility-combat}
You can easily move through a dangerous melee.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 13, [Dodge].

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +4 [dodge bonus] to @ref{#armor-class,Armor Class} against attacks of opportunity caused when you move out of or within a threatened area. A condition that makes you lose your [Dexterity] bonus to @ref{#armor-class,Armor Class} (if any) also makes you lose [dodge bonus]es.

[Dodge bonus]es stack with each other, unlike most types of bonuses.

@node Mounted Archery Combat
@section Mounted Archery (Combat)
@anchor{#mounted-archery-combat}
You are skilled at making ranged attacks while mounted.

@strong{Prerequisites:} Ride 1 rank, @ref{#mounted-combat,Mounted Combat}.

@strong{Benefit:} The penalty you take when using a ranged weapon while mounted is halved: --2 instead of --4 if your mount is taking a double move, and --4 instead of --8 if your mount is running.

@node Mounted Combat Combat
@section Mounted Combat (Combat)
@anchor{#mounted-combat-combat}
You are adept at guiding your mount through combat.

@strong{Prerequisite:} Ride 1 rank.

@strong{Benefit:} Once per round when your mount is hit in combat, you may attempt a Ride check (as an immediate action) to negate the hit. The hit is negated if your Ride check result is greater than the opponent's attack roll.

@node Natural Spell
@section Natural Spell
@anchor{#natural-spell}
You can cast spells even while in a form that cannot normally cast spells.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Wis] 13, wild shape class feature.

@strong{Benefit:} You can complete the verbal and somatic components of spells while using wild shape. You substitute various noises and gestures for the normal verbal and somatic components of a spell.

You can also use any material components or focuses you possess, even if such items are melded within your current form. This feat does not permit the use of magic items while you are in a form that could not ordinarily use them, and you do not gain the ability to speak while using wild shape.

@node Nimble Moves
@section Nimble Moves
@anchor{#nimble-moves}
You can move across a single obstacle with ease.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 13.

@strong{Benefit:} Whenever you move, you may move through 5 feet of difficult terrain each round as if it were normal terrain. This feat allows you to take a 5-foot step into difficult terrain.

@node Penetrating Strike Combat
@section Penetrating Strike (Combat)
@anchor{#penetrating-strike-combat}
Your attacks are capable of penetrating the defenses of some creatures.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Weapon Focus], base attack bonus +1, 12th-level fighter, proficiency with weapon.

@strong{Benefit:} Your attacks with weapons selected with [Weapon Focus] ignore up to 5 points of damage reduction. This feat does not apply to damage reduction without a type (such as DR 10/---).

@node Persuasive
@section Persuasive
@anchor{#persuasive}
You are skilled at swaying attitudes and intimidating others into your way of thinking.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +2 bonus on @ref{#diplomacy,Diplomacy} and @ref{#intimidate,Intimidate} skill checks. If you have 10 or more ranks in one of these skills, the bonus increases to +4 for that skill.

@node Pinpoint Targeting Combat
@section Pinpoint Targeting (Combat)
@anchor{#pinpoint-targeting-combat}
You can target the weak points in your opponent's armor.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 19, [Improved Precise Shot], [Point-Blank Shot], [Precise Shot], base attack bonus +16.

@strong{Benefit:} As a standard action, make a single ranged attack. The target does not gain any armor, natural armor, or shield bonuses to its @ref{#armor-class,Armor Class}. You do not gain the benefit of this feat if you move this round.

@node Point-Blank Shot Combat
@section Point-Blank Shot (Combat)
@anchor{#point-blank-shot-combat}
You are especially accurate when making ranged attacks against close targets.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls with ranged weapons at ranges of up to 30 feet.

@node Power Attack Combat
@section Power Attack (Combat)
@anchor{#power-attack-combat}
You can make exceptionally deadly melee attacks by sacrificing accuracy for strength.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Str] 13, base attack bonus +1.

@strong{Benefit:} You can choose to take a --1 penalty on all melee attack rolls and combat maneuver checks to gain a +2 bonus on all melee damage rolls. This bonus to damage is increased by half (+50%) if you are making an attack with a two-handed weapon, a one handed weapon using two hands, or a primary natural weapon that adds 1-1/2 times your Strength modifier on damage rolls. This bonus to damage is halved (--50%) if you are making an attack with an off-hand weapon or secondary natural weapon. When your base attack bonus reaches +4, and every 4 points thereafter, the penalty increases by --1 and the bonus to damage increases by +2. You must choose to use this feat before making an attack roll, and its effects last until your next turn. The bonus damage does not apply to touch attacks or effects that do not deal hit point damage.

@node Precise Shot Combat
@section Precise Shot (Combat)
@anchor{#precise-shot-combat}
You are adept at firing ranged attacks into melee.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Point-Blank Shot].

@strong{Benefit:} You can shoot or throw ranged weapons at an opponent engaged in melee without taking the standard --4 penalty on your attack roll.

@node Quick Draw Combat
@section Quick Draw (Combat)
@anchor{#quick-draw-combat}
You can draw weapons faster than most.

@strong{Prerequisite:} Base attack bonus +1.

@strong{Benefit:} You can draw a weapon as a free action instead of as a move action. You can draw a hidden weapon (see the @ref{#sleight-of-hand,Sleight of Hand} skill) as a move action.

A character who has selected this feat may throw weapons at his full normal rate of attacks (much like a character with a bow).

Alchemical items, potions, scrolls, and wands cannot be drawn quickly using this feat.

@strong{Normal:} Without this feat, you may draw a weapon as a move action, or (if your base attack bonus is +1 or higher) as a free action as part of movement. Without this feat, you can draw a hidden weapon as a standard action.

@node Quicken Spell Metamagic
@section Quicken Spell (Metamagic)
@anchor{#quicken-spell-metamagic}
You can cast spells in a fraction of the normal time.

@strong{Benefit:} Casting a quickened spell is a swift action. You can perform another action, even casting another spell, in the same round as you cast a quickened spell. A spell whose casting time is more than 1 round or 1 full-round action cannot be quickened.

A quickened spell uses up a spell slot four levels higher than the spell's actual level. Casting a quickened spell doesn't provoke an attack of opportunity.

@strong{Special:} You can apply the effects of this feat to a spell cast spontaneously, so long as it has a casting time that is not more than 1 full-round action, without increasing the spell's casting time.

@node Rapid Reload Combat
@section Rapid Reload (Combat)
@anchor{#rapid-reload-combat}
Choose a type of crossbow (hand, light, or heavy). You can reload such weapons quickly.

@strong{Prerequisite:} Weapon Proficiency (crossbow type chosen).

@strong{Benefit:} The time required for you to reload your chosen type of crossbow is reduced to a free action (for a hand or light crossbow) or a move action (for a heavy crossbow). Reloading a crossbow still provokes an attack of opportunity.

If you have selected this feat for hand crossbow or light crossbow, you may fire that weapon as many times in a full-attack action as you could attack if you were using a bow.

@strong{Normal:} A character without this feat needs a move action to reload a hand or light crossbow, or a full-round action to reload a heavy crossbow.

@strong{Special:} You can gain Rapid Reload multiple times. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new type of crossbow.

@node Rapid Shot Combat
@section Rapid Shot (Combat)
@anchor{#rapid-shot-combat}
You can make an additional ranged attack.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 13, [Point-Blank Shot].

@strong{Benefit:} When making a full-attack action with a ranged weapon, you can fire one additional time this round. All of your attack rolls take a --2 penalty when using Rapid Shot.

@node Ride-By Attack Combat
@section Ride-By Attack (Combat)
@anchor{#ride-by-attack-combat}
While mounted and charging, you can move, strike at a foe, and then continue moving.

@strong{Prerequisites:} Ride 1 rank, @ref{#mounted-combat,Mounted Combat}.

@strong{Benefit:} When you are mounted and use the charge action, you may move and attack as if with a standard charge and then move again (continuing the straight line of the charge). Your total movement for the round can't exceed double your mounted speed. You and your mount do not provoke an attack of opportunity from the opponent that you attack.

@node Run
@section Run
@anchor{#run}
You are swift of foot.

@strong{Benefit:} When running, you move five times your normal speed (if wearing medium, light, or no armor and carrying no more than a medium load) or four times your speed (if wearing heavy armor or carrying a heavy load). If you make a jump after a running start (see the Acrobatics skill description), you gain a +4 bonus on your Acrobatics check. While running, you retain your [Dexterity] bonus to your @ref{#armor-class,Armor Class}.

@strong{Normal:} You move four times your speed while running (if wearing medium, light, or no armor and carrying no more than a medium load) or three times your speed (if wearing heavy armor or carrying a heavy load), and you lose your [Dexterity] bonus to [AC].

@node Scorpion Style Combat
@section Scorpion Style (Combat)
@anchor{#scorpion-style-combat}
You can perform an unarmed strike that greatly hampers your target's movement.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Improved Unarmed Strike].

@strong{Benefit:} To use this feat, you must make a single unarmed attack as a standard action. If this unarmed attack hits, you deal damage normally, and the target's base land speed is reduced to 5 feet for a number of rounds equal to your [Wisdom] modifier unless it makes a [Fortitude] saving throw (DC 10 + 1/2 your character level + your [Wis] modifier).

@node Scribe Scroll Item Creation
@section Scribe Scroll (Item Creation)
@anchor{#scribe-scroll-item-creation}
You can create magic scrolls.

@strong{Prerequisite:} Caster level 1st.

@strong{Benefit:} You can create a scroll of any spell that you know. Scribing a scroll takes 2 hours if its base price is 250 gp or less, otherwise scribing a scroll takes 1 day for each 1,000 gp in its base price. To scribe a scroll, you must use up raw materials costing half of this base price. See the magic item creation rules in [Magic Items] for more information.

@node Selective Channeling
@section Selective Channeling
@anchor{#selective-channeling}
You can choose whom to affect when you channel energy.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Cha] 13, channel energy class feature.

@strong{Benefit:} When you channel energy, you can choose a number of targets in the area up to your [Charisma] modifier. These targets are not affected by your channeled energy.

@strong{Normal:} All targets in a 30-foot burst are affected when you channel energy. You can only choose whether or not you are affected.

@node Self-Sufficient
@section Self-Sufficient
@anchor{#self-sufficient}
You know how to get along in the wild and how to effectively treat wounds.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +2 bonus on all @ref{#heal,Heal} checks and @ref{#survival,Survival} checks. If you have 10 or more ranks in one of these skills, the bonus increases to +4 for that skill.

@node Shatter Defenses Combat
@section Shatter Defenses (Combat)
@anchor{#shatter-defenses-combat}
Your skill with your chosen weapon leaves opponents unable to defend themselves if you strike them when their defenses are already compromised.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Weapon Focus], [Dazzling Display], base attack bonus +6, proficiency with weapon.

@strong{Benefit:} Any [shaken], [frightened], or [panicked] opponent hit by you this round is [flat-footed] to your attacks until the end of your next turn. This includes any additional attacks you make this round.

@node Shield Focus Combat
@section Shield Focus (Combat)
@anchor{#shield-focus-combat}
You are skilled at deflecting blows with your shield.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Shield Proficiency], base attack bonus +1.

@strong{Benefit:} Increase the [AC] bonus granted by any shield you are using by 1.

@node Shield Master Combat
@section Shield Master (Combat)
@anchor{#shield-master-combat}
Your mastery of the shield allows you to fight with it without hindrance.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Improved Shield Bash], [Shield Proficiency], [Shield Slam], @ref{#two-weapon-fighting,Two-Weapon Fighting}, base attack bonus +11.

@strong{Benefit:} You do not suffer any penalties on attack rolls made with a shield while you are wielding another weapon. Add your shield's enhancement bonus to attacks and damage rolls made with the shield as if it was a weapon enhancement bonus.

@node Shield Proficiency Combat
@section Shield Proficiency (Combat)
@anchor{#shield-proficiency-combat}
You are trained in how to properly use a shield.

@strong{Benefit:} When you use a shield (except a tower shield), the shield's armor check penalty only applies to Strength- and [Dexterity]-based skills.

@strong{Normal:} When you are using a shield with which you are not proficient, you take the shield's armor check penalty on attack rolls and on all skill checks that involve moving.

@strong{Special:} Barbarians, bards, clerics, druids, fighters, paladins, and rangers all automatically have Shield Proficiency as a bonus feat. They need not select it.

@node Shield Slam Combat
@section Shield Slam (Combat)
@anchor{#shield-slam-combat}
In the right position, your shield can be used to send opponents flying.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Improved Shield Bash], [Shield Proficiency], @ref{#two-weapon-fighting,Two-Weapon Fighting}, base attack bonus +6.

@strong{Benefit:} Any opponents hit by your shield bash are also hit with a free [bull rush] attack, substituting your attack roll for the combat maneuver check (see [Combat] does not provoke an attack of opportunity. Opponents who cannot move back due to a wall or other surface are knocked [prone] after moving the maximum possible distance. You may choose to move with your target if you are able to take a 5-foot step or to spend an action to move this turn.

@node Shot on the Run Combat
@section Shot on the Run (Combat)
@anchor{#shot-on-the-run-combat}
You can move, fire a ranged weapon, and move again before your foes can react.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 13, [Dodge], [Mobility], [Point-Blank Shot], base attack bonus +4.

@strong{Benefit:} As a full-round action, you can move up to your speed and make a single ranged attack at any point during your movement.

@strong{Normal:} You cannot move before and after an attack with a ranged weapon.

@node Sickening Critical Combat Critical
@section Sickening Critical (Combat, Critical)
@anchor{#sickening-critical-combat-critical}
Your critical hits cause opponents to become sickened.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Critical Focus], base attack bonus +11.

@strong{Benefit:} Whenever you score a critical hit, your opponent becomes [sickened] for 1 minute. The effects of this feat do not stack. Additional hits instead add to the effect's duration.

@strong{Special:} You can only apply the effects of one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery.

@node Silent Spell Metamagic
@section Silent Spell (Metamagic)
@anchor{#silent-spell-metamagic}
You can cast your spells without making any sound.

@strong{Benefit:} A silent spell can be cast with no verbal components. Spells without verbal components are not affected. A silent spell uses up a spell slot one level higher than the spell's actual level.

@strong{Special:} Bard spells cannot be enhanced by this feat.

@node Simple Weapon Proficiency Combat
@section Simple Weapon Proficiency (Combat)
@anchor{#simple-weapon-proficiency-combat}
@{#simple-weapon-proficiency@}

You are trained in the use of basic weapons.

@strong{Benefit:} You make attack rolls with simple weapons without penalty.

@strong{Normal:} When using a weapon with which you are not proficient, you take a --4 penalty on attack rolls.

@strong{Special:} All characters except for druids, monks, and wizards are automatically proficient with all simple weapons. They need not select this feat.

@node Skill Focus
@section Skill Focus
@anchor{#skill-focus}
Choose a skill. You are particularly adept at that skill.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +3 bonus on all checks involving the chosen skill. If you have 10 or more ranks in that skill, this bonus increases to +6.

@strong{Special:} You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new skill.

@node Snatch Arrows Combat
@section Snatch Arrows (Combat)
@anchor{#snatch-arrows-combat}
Instead of knocking an arrow or ranged attack aside, you can catch it in mid-flight.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 15, [Deflect Arrows], [Improved Unarmed Strike].

@strong{Benefit:} When using the [Deflect Arrows] feat you may choose to catch the weapon instead of just deflecting it. Thrown weapons can immediately be thrown back as an attack against the original attacker (even though it isn't your turn) or kept for later use.

You must have at least one hand free (holding nothing) to use this feat.

@node Spell Focus
@section Spell Focus
@anchor{#spell-focus}
Choose a school of magic. Any spells you cast of that school are more difficult to resist.

@strong{Benefit:} Add +1 to the Difficulty Class for all saving throws against spells from the school of magic you select.

@strong{Special:} You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new school of magic.

@node Spell Mastery
@section Spell Mastery
@anchor{#spell-mastery}
You have mastered a small handful of spells, and can prepare these spells without referencing your spellbooks at all.

@strong{Prerequisite:} 1st-level wizard

@strong{Benefit:} Each time you take this feat, choose a number of spells that you already know equal to your [Intelligence] modifier. From that point on, you can prepare these spells without referring to a spellbook.

@strong{Normal:} Without this feat, you must use a spellbook to prepare all your spells, except @emph{read magic.}

@node Spell Penetration
@section Spell Penetration
@anchor{#spell-penetration}
Your spells break through spell resistance more easily than most.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +2 bonus on caster level checks (1d20 + caster level) made to overcome a creature's [spell resistance].

@node Spellbreaker Combat
@section Spellbreaker (Combat)
@anchor{#spellbreaker-combat}
You can strike at enemy spellcasters who fail to cast defensively when you threaten them.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Disruptive], 10th-level fighter.

@strong{Benefit:} Enemies in your threatened area that fail their checks to cast spells defensively provoke attacks of opportunity from you.

@strong{Normal:} Enemies that fail to cast spells defensively do not provoke attacks of opportunity.

@node Spirited Charge Combat
@section Spirited Charge (Combat)
@anchor{#spirited-charge-combat}
Your mounted charge attacks deal a tremendous amount of damage.

@strong{Prerequisites:} Ride 1 rank, @ref{#mounted-combat,Mounted Combat}, Ride-By Attack.

@strong{Benefit:} When mounted and using the charge action, you deal double damage with a melee weapon (or triple damage with a lance).

@node Spring Attack Combat
@section Spring Attack (Combat)
@anchor{#spring-attack-combat}
You can deftly move up to a foe, strike, and withdraw before he can react.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 13, [Dodge], [Mobility], base attack bonus +4.

@strong{Benefit:} As a full-round action, you can move up to your speed and make a single melee attack without provoking any attacks of opportunity from the target of your attack. You can move both before and after the attack, but you must move at least 10 feet before the attack and the total distance that you move cannot be greater than your speed. You cannot use this ability to attack a foe that is adjacent to you at the start of your turn.

@strong{Normal:} You cannot move before and after an attack.

@node Staggering Critical Combat Critical
@section Staggering Critical (Combat, Critical)
@anchor{#staggering-critical-combat-critical}
Your critical hits cause opponents to slow down.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Critical Focus], base attack bonus +13.

@strong{Benefit:} Whenever you score a critical hit, your opponent becomes [staggered] for 1d4+1 rounds. A successful [Fortitude] save reduces the duration to 1 round. The DC of this [Fortitude] save is equal to 10 + your base attack bonus. The effects of this feat do not stack. Additional hits instead add to the duration.

@strong{Special:} You can only apply the effects of one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery.

@node Stand Still Combat
@section Stand Still (Combat)
@anchor{#stand-still-combat}
You can stop foes that try to move past you.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Combat Reflexes].

@strong{Benefit:} When a foe provokes an attack of opportunity due to moving through your adjacent squares, you can make a combat maneuver check as your attack of opportunity. If successful, the enemy cannot move for the rest of his turn. An enemy can still take the rest of his action, but cannot move. This feat also applies to any creature that attempts to move from a square that is adjacent to you if such movement provokes an attack of opportunity.

@node Stealthy
@section Stealthy
@anchor{#stealthy}
You are good at avoiding unwanted attention and slipping out of bonds.

@strong{Benefit:} You get a +2 bonus on all @ref{#escape-artist,Escape Artist} and @ref{#stealth,Stealth} skill checks. If you have 10 or more ranks in one of these skills, the bonus increases to +4 for that skill.

@node Step Up Combat
@section Step Up (Combat)
@anchor{#step-up-combat}
You can close the distance when a foe tries to move away.

@strong{Prerequisite:} Base attack bonus +1.

@strong{Benefit:} Whenever an adjacent foe attempts to take a 5-foot step away from you, you may also make a 5-foot step as an immediate action so long as you end up adjacent to the foe that triggered this ability. If you take this step, you cannot take a 5-foot step during your next turn. If you take an action to move during your next turn, subtract 5 feet from your total movement.

@node Still Spell Metamagic
@section Still Spell (Metamagic)
@anchor{#still-spell-metamagic}
You can cast spells without moving.

@strong{Benefit:} A stilled spell can be cast with no somatic components. Spells without somatic components are not affected. A stilled spell uses up a spell slot one level higher than the spell's actual level.

@node Strike Back Combat
@section Strike Back (Combat)
@anchor{#strike-back-combat}
You can strike at foes that attack you using their superior reach, by targeting their limbs or weapons as they come at you.

@strong{Prerequisite:} Base attack bonus +11.

@strong{Benefit:} You can ready an action to make a melee attack against any foe that attacks you in melee, even if the foe is outside of your reach.

@node Stunning Critical Combat Critical
@section Stunning Critical (Combat, Critical)
@anchor{#stunning-critical-combat-critical}
Your critical hits cause opponents to become stunned.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Critical Focus], [Staggering Critical], base attack bonus +17.

@strong{Benefit:} Whenever you score a critical hit, your opponent becomes [stunned] for 1d4 rounds. A successful [Fortitude] save reduces this to [staggered] for 1d4 rounds. The DC of this [Fortitude] save is equal to 10 + your base attack bonus. The effects of this feat do not stack. Additional hits instead add to the duration.

@strong{Special:} You can only apply the effects of one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery.

@node Stunning Fist Combat
@section Stunning Fist (Combat)
@anchor{#stunning-fist-combat}
You know just where to strike to temporarily stun a foe.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 13, [Wis] 13, [Improved Unarmed Strike], base attack bonus +8.

@strong{Benefit:} You must declare that you are using this feat before you make your attack roll (thus, a failed attack roll ruins the attempt). Stunning Fist forces a foe damaged by your unarmed attack to make a [Fortitude] saving throw (DC 10 + 1/2 your character level + your [Wis] modifier), in addition to dealing damage normally. A defender who fails this saving throw is [stunned] for 1 round (until just before your next turn). A stunned character drops everything held, can't take actions, loses any [Dexterity] bonus to [AC], and takes a --2 penalty to [AC]. You may attempt a stunning attack once per day for every four levels you have attained (but see Special), and no more than once per round. Constructs, oozes, plants, undead, [incorporeal] creatures, and creatures immune to critical hits cannot be [stunned].

@strong{Special:} A monk receives Stunning Fist as a bonus feat at 1st level, even if he does not meet the prerequisites. A monk may attempt a stunning attack a number of times per day equal to his monk level, plus one more time per day for every four levels he has in classes other than monk.

@node Throw Anything Combat
@section Throw Anything (Combat)
@anchor{#throw-anything-combat}
You are used to throwing things you have on hand.

@strong{Benefit:} You do not suffer any penalties for using an improvised ranged weapon. You receive a +1 circumstance bonus on attack rolls made with thrown splash weapons.

@strong{Normal:} You take a --4 penalty on attack rolls made with an improvised weapon.

@node Tiring Critical Combat Critical
@section Tiring Critical (Combat, Critical)
@anchor{#tiring-critical-combat-critical}
Your critical hits cause opponents to become fatigued.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Critical Focus], base attack bonus +13.

@strong{Benefit:} Whenever you score a critical hit, your opponent becomes [fatigued]. This feat has no additional effect on a [fatigued] or [exhausted] creature.

@strong{Special:} You can only apply the effects of one critical feat to a given critical hit unless you possess Critical Mastery.

@node Toughness
@section Toughness
@anchor{#toughness}
You have enhanced physical stamina.

@strong{Benefit:} You gain +3 hit points. For every Hit Die you possess beyond 3, you gain an additional +1 hit point. If you have more than 3 Hit Dice, you gain +1 hit points whenever you gain a Hit Die (such as when you gain a level).

@node Tower Shield Proficiency Combat
@section Tower Shield Proficiency (Combat)
@anchor{#tower-shield-proficiency-combat}
You are trained in how to properly use a tower shield.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Shield Proficiency].

@strong{Benefit:} When you use a tower shield, the shield's armor check penalty only applies to Strength and [Dexterity]-based skills.

@strong{Normal:} A character using a shield with which he is not proficient takes the shield's armor check penalty on attack rolls and on all skill checks that involve moving, including Ride.

@strong{Special:} Fighters automatically have Tower Shield Proficiency as a bonus feat. They need not select it.

@node Trample Combat
@section Trample (Combat)
@anchor{#trample-combat}
While mounted, you can ride down opponents and trample them under your mount.

@strong{Prerequisites:} Ride 1 rank, @ref{#mounted-combat,Mounted Combat}.

@strong{Benefit:} When you attempt to [overrun] an opponent while mounted, your target may not choose to avoid you. Your mount may make one hoof attack against any target you knock down, gaining the standard +4 bonus on attack rolls against prone targets.

@node Turn Undead
@section Turn Undead
@anchor{#turn-undead}
Calling upon higher powers, you cause undead to flee from the might of your unleashed divine energy.

@strong{Prerequisites:} Channel positive energy class feature.

@strong{Benefit:} You can, as a standard action, use one of your uses of channel positive energy to cause all undead within 30 feet of you to flee, as if [panicked]. Undead receive a [Will] save to negate the effect. The DC for this [Will] save is equal to 10 + 1/2 your cleric level + your [Charisma] modifier. Undead that fail their save flee for 1 minute. Intelligent undead receive a new saving throw each round to end the effect. If you use channel energy in this way, it has no other effect (it does not heal or harm nearby creatures).

@node Two-Weapon Defense Combat
@section Two-Weapon Defense (Combat)
@anchor{#two-weapon-defense-combat}
You are skilled at defending yourself while dual-wielding.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 15, @ref{#two-weapon-fighting,Two-Weapon Fighting}.

@strong{Benefit:} When wielding a double weapon or two weapons (not including natural weapons or unarmed strikes), you gain a +1 shield bonus to your [AC].

When you are fighting defensively or using the total defense action, this shield bonus increases to +2.

@node Two-Weapon Fighting Combat
@section Two-Weapon Fighting (Combat)
@anchor{#two-weapon-fighting-combat}
You can fight with a weapon wielded in each of your hands. You can make one extra attack each round with the secondary weapon.

@strong{Prerequisite:} [Dex] 15.

@strong{Benefit:} Your penalties on attack rolls for fighting with two weapons are reduced. The penalty for your primary hand lessens by 2 and the one for your off hand lessens by 6. See Two-Weapon Fighting in [Combat].

@strong{Normal:} If you wield a second weapon in your off hand, you can get one extra attack per round with that weapon. When fighting in this way you suffer a --6 penalty with your regular attack or attacks with your primary hand and a --10 penalty to the attack with your off hand. If your off-hand weapon is light, the penalties are reduced by 2 each. An unarmed strike is always considered light.

@node Two-Weapon Rend Combat
@section Two-Weapon Rend (Combat)
@anchor{#two-weapon-rend-combat}
Striking with both of your weapons simultaneously, you can use them to deliver devastating wounds.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 17, [Double Slice], [Improved Two-Weapon Fighting], @ref{#two-weapon-fighting,Two-Weapon Fighting}, base attack bonus +11.

@strong{Benefit:} If you hit an opponent with both your primary hand and your off-hand weapon, you deal an additional 1d10 points of damage plus 1-1/2 times your Strength modifier. You can only deal this additional damage once each round.

@node Unseat Combat
@section Unseat (Combat)
@anchor{#unseat-combat}
You are skilled at unseating your mounted opponents.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Str] 13, Ride 1 rank, @ref{#mounted-combat,Mounted Combat}, [Power Attack], [Improved Bull Rush], base attack bonus +1.

@strong{Benefits:} When charging an opponent while mounted and wielding a lance, resolve the attack as normal. If it hits, you may immediately make a free [bull rush] attempt in addition to the normal damage. If successful, the target is knocked off his horse and lands [prone] in a space adjacent to his mount that is directly away from you.

@node Vital Strike Combat
@section Vital Strike (Combat)
@anchor{#vital-strike-combat}
You make a single attack that deals significantly more damage than normal.

@strong{Prerequisites:} Base attack bonus +6.

@strong{Benefit:} When you use the attack action, you can make one attack at your highest base attack bonus that deals additional damage. Roll the weapon's damage dice for the attack twice and add the results together before adding bonuses from Strength, weapon abilities (such as [@emph{flaming}]), precision based damage, and other damage bonuses. These extra weapon damage dice are not multiplied on a critical hit, but are added to the total.

@node Weapon Finesse Combat
@section Weapon Finesse (Combat)
@anchor{#weapon-finesse-combat}
You are trained in using your agility in melee combat, as opposed to brute strength.

@strong{Benefit:} With a light weapon, rapier, whip, or spiked chain made for a creature of your size category, you may use your [Dexterity] modifier instead of your Strength modifier on attack rolls. If you carry a shield, its armor check penalty applies to your attack rolls.

@strong{Special:} Natural weapons are considered light weapons.

@node Weapon Focus Combat
@section Weapon Focus (Combat)
@anchor{#weapon-focus-combat}
Choose one type of weapon. You can also choose unarmed strike or [grapple] (or ray, if you are a spellcaster) as your weapon for the purposes of this feat.

@strong{Prerequisites:} Proficiency with selected weapon, base attack bonus +1.

@strong{Benefit:} You gain a +1 bonus on all attack rolls you make using the selected weapon.

@strong{Special:} You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new type of weapon.

@node Weapon Specialization Combat
@section Weapon Specialization (Combat)
@anchor{#weapon-specialization-combat}
You are skilled at dealing damage with one weapon. Choose one type of weapon (including unarmed strike or [grapple]) for which you have already selected the [Weapon Focus] feat. You deal extra damage when using this weapon.

@strong{Prerequisites:} Proficiency with selected weapon, [Weapon Focus] with selected weapon, fighter level 4th.

@strong{Benefit:} You gain a +2 bonus on all damage rolls you make using the selected weapon.

@strong{Special:} You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new type of weapon.

@node Whirlwind Attack Combat
@section Whirlwind Attack (Combat)
@anchor{#whirlwind-attack-combat}
You can strike out at every foe within reach.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 13, [Int] 13, [Combat Expertise], [Dodge], [Mobility], [Spring Attack], base attack bonus +4.

@strong{Benefit:} When you use the full-attack action, you can give up your regular attacks and instead make one melee attack at your highest base attack bonus against each opponent within reach. You must make a separate attack roll against each opponent.

When you use the Whirlwind Attack feat, you also forfeit any bonus or extra attacks granted by other feats, spells, or abilities.

@node Widen Spell Metamagic
@section Widen Spell (Metamagic)
@anchor{#widen-spell-metamagic}
You can cast your spells so that they occupy a larger space.

@strong{Benefit:} You can alter a burst, emanation, or spread-shaped spell to increase its area. Any numeric measurements of the spell's area increase by 100%. A widened spell uses up a spell slot three levels higher than the spell's actual level.

Spells that do not have an area of one of these four sorts are not affected by this feat.

@node Wind Stance Combat
@section Wind Stance (Combat)
@anchor{#wind-stance-combat}
Your erratic movements make it difficult for enemies to pinpoint your location.

@strong{Prerequisites:} [Dex] 15, [Dodge], base attack bonus +6.

@strong{Benefit:} If you move more than 5 feet this turn, you gain 20% concealment for 1 round against ranged attacks.

