@strong{Hallow}

@strong{School} evocation [good]; @strong{Level} cleric 5, druid 5

@strong{Casting Time} 24 hours

@strong{Components} V, S, M (herbs, oils, and incense worth at least 1,000 gp, plus 1,000 gp per level of the spell to be included in the @emph{hallowed}area), DF

@strong{Range} touch

@strong{Area} 40-ft. radius emanating from the touched point

@strong{Duration} instantaneous

@strong{Saving Throw} see text; @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} see text

@emph{Hallow}makes a particular site, building, or structure a holy site. This has four major effects.

First, the site is warded by a @emph{[magic circle against evil]}effect.

Second, the DC to resist positive channeled energy within this area gains a +4 sacred bonus and the DC to resist negative energy is reduced by 4. [Spell resistance] does not apply to this effect. This provision does not apply to the druid version of the spell.

Third, any dead body interred in a @emph{hallowed}site cannot be turned into an undead creature.

Finally, you can fix a single spell effect to the @emph{hallowed}site. The spell effect lasts for 1 year and functions throughout the entire site, regardless of the normal duration and area or effect. You may designate whether the effect applies to all creatures, creatures who share your faith or alignment, or creatures who adhere to another faith or alignment. At the end of the year, the chosen effect lapses, but it can be renewed or replaced simply by casting @emph{hallow}again.

Spell effects that may be tied to a @emph{hallowed}site include @emph{[aid], [bane], [bless], [cause fear], [darkness], [daylight], [death ward], [deeper darkness], [detect evil], [detect magic], [dimensional anchor], [discern lies], [dispel magic], [endure elements], [freedom of movement], [invisibility purge], [protection from energy], [remove fear], [resist energy], [silence], [tongues],}and @emph{[zone of truth]}. Saving throws and [spell resistance] might apply to these spells' effects. (See the individual spell descriptions for details.)

An area can receive only one @emph{hallow}spell (and its associated spell effect) at a time. @emph{Hallow}counters but does not dispel @emph{[unhallow]}.

Hallucinatory Terrain

@strong{Hallucinatory Terrain}

@strong{School} illusion (glamer); @strong{Level} bard 4, sorcerer/wizard 4

@strong{Casting Time} 10 minutes

@strong{Components} V, S, M (a stone, a twig, and a green leaf)

@strong{Range} long (400 ft. + 40 ft./level)

@strong{Area} one 30-ft. cube/level (S)

@strong{Duration} 2 hours/level (D)

@strong{Saving Throw}[Will] disbelief (if interacted with); @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} no

You make natural terrain look, sound, and smell like some other sort of natural terrain. Structures, equipment, and creatures within the area are not hidden or changed in appearance.

Halt Undead

@strong{Halt Undead}

@strong{School} necromancy; @strong{Level} sorcerer/wizard 3

@strong{Casting Time} 1 standard action

@strong{Components} V, S, M (a pinch of sulfur and powdered garlic)

@strong{Range}medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)

@strong{Targets} up to three undead creatures, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart

@strong{Duration} 1 round/level

@strong{Saving Throw}[Will] negates (see text); @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} yes

This spell renders as many as three undead creatures immobile. A nonintelligent undead creature gets no saving throw; an intelligent undead creature does. If the spell is successful, it renders the undead creature immobile for the duration of the spell (similar to the effect of @emph{[hold person]}on a living creature). The effect is broken if the @emph{halted}creatures are attacked or take damage.

Harm

@strong{Harm}

@strong{School} necromancy; @strong{Level} cleric 6

@strong{Casting Time} 1 standard action

@strong{Components} V, S

@strong{Range} touch

@strong{Target} creature touched

@strong{Duration} instantaneous

@strong{Saving Throw}[Will] half; see text; @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} yes

@emph{Harm}charges a subject with negative energy that deals 10 points of damage per caster level (to a maximum of 150 points at 15th level). If the creature successfully saves, @emph{harm}deals half this amount. @emph{Harm} cannot reduce the target's hit points to less than 1.

If used on an undead creature, @emph{harm}acts like @emph{[heal]}.

Haste

@strong{Haste}

@strong{School} transmutation; @strong{Level} bard 3, sorcerer/wizard 3

@strong{Casting Time} 1 standard action

@strong{Components} V, S, M (a shaving of licorice root)

@strong{Range} close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)

@strong{Targets} one creature/level, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart

@strong{Duration} 1 round/level

@strong{Saving Throw} [Fortitude] negates (harmless); @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} yes (harmless)

The transmuted creatures move and act more quickly than normal. This extra speed has several effects.

When making a full attack action, a hasted creature may make one extra attack with one natural or manufactured weapon. The attack is made using the creature's full base attack bonus, plus any modifiers appropriate to the situation. (This effect is not cumulative with similar effects, such as that provided by a @emph{speed} weapon, nor does it actually grant an extra action, so you can't use it to cast a second spell or otherwise take an extra action in the round.)

A hasted creature gains a +1 bonus on attack rolls and a +1 [dodge bonus] to [AC] and [Reflex] saves. Any condition that makes you lose your [Dexterity] bonus to @ref{#armor-class,Armor Class} (if any) also makes you lose [dodge bonus]es.

All of the hasted creature's modes of movement (including land movement, burrow, climb, fly, and swim) increase by 30 feet, to a maximum of twice the subject's normal speed using that form of movement. This increase counts as an enhancement bonus, and it affects the creature's jumping distance as normal for increased speed. Multiple @emph{haste}effects don't stack. @emph{Haste}dispels and counters @emph{[slow].}

Heal

@strong{Heal}

@strong{School} conjuration (healing); @strong{Level} cleric 6, druid 7

@strong{Casting Time} 1 standard action

@strong{Components} V, S

@strong{Range} touch

@strong{Target} creature touched

@strong{Duration} instantaneous

@strong{Saving Throw}[Will] negates (harmless); @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} yes (harmless)

@emph{Heal}enables you to channel positive energy into a creature to wipe away injury and afflictions. It immediately ends any and all of the following adverse conditions affecting the target: ability damage, [blinded], [confused]@emph{,}[dazed], [dazzled], [deafened], diseased, [exhausted], [fatigued], [feeblemind]ed@emph{,}[insanity], [nauseated], poisoned, [sickened], and [stunned]. It also cures 10 hit points of damage per level of the caster, to a maximum of 150 points at 15th level.

@emph{Heal}does not remove [negative levels] or restore permanently drained ability score points.

If used against an undead creature, @emph{heal}instead acts like @emph{[harm]}.

@strong{Heal, Mass}

@strong{School} conjuration (healing); @strong{Level} cleric 9

@strong{Range} close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)

@strong{Targets} one or more creatures, no two of which can be more than 30 ft. apart

This spell functions like @emph{[heal],}except as noted above. The maximum number of hit points restored to each creature is 250.

Heal Mount

@strong{Heal Mount}

@strong{School} conjuration (healing); @strong{Level} paladin 3

@strong{Casting Time} 1 standard action

@strong{Components} V, S

@strong{Range} touch

@strong{Target} your mount touched

@strong{Duration} instantaneous

@strong{Saving Throw}[Will] negates (harmless); @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} yes (harmless)

This spell functions like @emph{[heal],}but it affects only the paladin's special mount (typically a horse).

Heat Metal

@strong{Heat Metal}

@strong{School} transmutation [fire]; @strong{Level} druid 2

