@node Attack Roll
@section Attack Roll
@anchor{#attack-roll}
An attack roll represents your attempt to strike your opponent on your turn in a round. When you make an attack roll, you roll a d20 and add your attack bonus. (Other modifiers may also apply to this roll.) If your result equals or beats the target's @ref{#armor-class,Armor Class}, you hit and deal damage.

@strong{Automatic Misses and Hits}: A natural 1 (the d20 comes up 1) on an attack roll is always a miss. A natural 20 (the d20 comes up 20) is always a hit. A natural 20 is also a threat---a possible critical hit ).

@node Attack Bonus
@section Attack Bonus
@anchor{#attack-bonus}
Your attack bonus with a melee weapon is the following:

@strong{Base attack bonus + [Strength] modifier + size modifier}

With a ranged weapon, your attack bonus is the following:

@strong{Base attack bonus + [Dexterity] modifier + size modifier + range penalty}

@node Armor Class
@section Armor Class
@anchor{#armor-class}
Your Armor Class (AC) represents how hard it is for opponents to land a solid, damaging blow on you. It's the attack roll result that an opponent needs to achieve to hit you. Your AC is equal to the following:

@strong{10 + armor bonus + shield bonus + [Dexterity] modifier + other modifiers}

Note that armor limits your [Dexterity] bonus, so if you're wearing armor, you might not be able to apply your whole [Dexterity] bonus to your AC (see [Table: Armor and Shields]).

Sometimes you can't use your [Dexterity] bonus (if you have one). If you can't react to a blow, you can't use your [Dexterity] bonus to AC. If you don't have a [Dexterity] bonus, your AC does not change.

@strong{Other Modifiers}: Many other factors modify your AC.

@emph{Enhancement Bonuses}: Enhancement bonuses apply to your armor to increase the armor bonus it provides.

@emph{Deflection Bonus}: Magical deflection effects ward off attacks and improve your AC.

@emph{Natural Armor}: If your race has a tough hide, scales, or thick skin you receive a bonus to your AC.

@emph{Dodge Bonuses}: Dodge bonuses represent actively avoiding blows. Any situation that denies you your [Dexterity] bonus also denies you dodge bonuses. (Wearing armor, however, does not limit these bonuses the way it limits a [Dexterity] bonus to AC.) Unlike most sorts of bonuses, dodge bonuses stack with each other.

