@strong{School} abjuration; @strong{Level} bard 1, cleric 3, sorcerer/wizard 2

@strong{Casting Time} 1 standard action

@strong{Components} V, S, M/DF (chameleon skin)

@strong{Range} touch

@strong{Target} one object touched of up to 100 lbs./level

@strong{Duration} 8 hours (D)

@strong{Saving Throw}[Will] negates (object); @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} yes (object)

This spell hides an object from location by divination (scrying) effects, such as the @emph{[scrying]}spell or a @emph{crystal ball}. Such an attempt automatically fails (if the divination is targeted on the object) or fails to perceive the object (if the divination is targeted on a nearby location, object, or person).

Obscuring Mist

@strong{Obscuring Mist}

@strong{School} conjuration (creation); @strong{Level} cleric 1, druid 1, sorcerer/wizard 1

@strong{Casting Time} 1 standard action

@strong{Components} V, S

@strong{Range} 20 ft.

@strong{Effect} cloud spreads in 20-ft. radius from you, 20 ft. high

@strong{Duration} 1 min./level (D)

@strong{Saving Throw} none; @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} no

A misty vapor arises around you. It is stationary. The vapor obscures all sight, including [darkvision], beyond 5 feet. A creature 5 feet away has concealment (attacks have a 20% miss chance). Creatures farther away have total concealment (50% miss chance, and the attacker cannot use sight to locate the target).

A moderate wind (11+ mph), such as from a @emph{[gust of wind]}spell, disperses the fog in 4 rounds. A strong wind (21+ mph) disperses the fog in 1 round. A @emph{[fireball], [flame strike]}, or similar spell burns away the fog in the explosive or fiery spell's area. A @emph{[wall of fire]}burns away the fog in the area into which it deals damage.

This spell does not function underwater.

Open/Close

@strong{Open/Close}

@strong{School} transmutation; @strong{Level} bard 0, sorcerer/wizard 0

@strong{Casting Time} 1 standard action

@strong{Components} V, S, F (a brass key)

@strong{Range} close (25 ft. + 5 ft./2 levels)

@strong{Target} object weighing up to 30 lbs. or portal that can be opened or closed

@strong{Duration} instantaneous

@strong{Saving Throw}[Will] negates (object); @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} yes (object)

You can open or close (your choice) a door, chest, box, window, bag, pouch, bottle, barrel, or other container. If anything resists this activity (such as a bar on a door or a lock on a chest), the spell fails. In addition, the spell can only open and close things weighing 30 pounds or less. Thus, doors, chests, and similar objects sized for enormous creatures may be beyond this spell's ability to affect.

Order's Wrath

@strong{Order's Wrath}

@strong{School} evocation [lawful]; @strong{Level} cleric 4

@strong{Casting Time} 1 standard action

@strong{Components} V, S

@strong{Range}medium (100 ft. + 10 ft./level)

@strong{Area} nonlawful creatures within a burst that fills a 30-ft. cube

@strong{Duration} instantaneous (1 round); see text

@strong{Saving Throw}[Will] partial; see text; @strong{@ref{#spell-resistance,Spell Resistance}} yes

You channel lawful power to smite enemies. The power takes the form of a three-dimensional grid of energy. Only chaotic and neutral (not lawful) creatures are harmed by the spell.

The spell deals 1d8 points of damage per two caster levels (maximum 5d8) to chaotic creatures (or 1d6 points of damage per caster level, maximum 10d6, to chaotic outsiders) and causes them to be [dazed] for 1 round. A successful [Will] save reduces the damage to half and negates the daze effect.

The spell deals only half damage to creatures who are neither chaotic nor lawful, and they are not [dazed]. They can reduce the damage in half again (down to one-quarter of the roll) with a successful [Will] save.

Overland Flight

@strong{Overland Flight}

@strong{School} transmutation; @strong{Level} sorcerer/wizard 5

@strong{Components}: V, S

@strong{Range} personal

@strong{Target} you

@strong{Duration} 1 hour/level

This spell functions like a @emph{[fly]}spell, except you can fly at a speed of 40 feet (30 feet if wearing medium or heavy armor, or if carrying a medium or heavy load) with a bonus on @ref{#fly,Fly} skill checks equal to half your caster level. When using this spell for long-distance movement, you can hustle without taking nonlethal damage (a forced march still requires [Constitution] checks). This means you can cover 64 miles in an 8-hour period of flight (or 48 miles at a speed of 30 feet).

