@* ## Ability Score Bonuses

Some spells and abilities increase your ability scores. Ability score increases with a duration of 1 day or less give only temporary bonuses. For every two points of increase to a single ability, apply a +1 bonus to the skills and statistics listed with the relevant ability.

@strong{[Strength]}: Temporary increases to your [Strength] score give you a bonus on [Strength]-based skill checks, melee attack rolls, and weapon damage rolls (if they rely on [Strength]). The bonus also applies to your [Combat Maneuver Bonus] (if you are Small or larger) and to your [Combat Maneuver Defense].

@strong{[Dexterity]}: Temporary increases to your [Dexterity] score give you a bonus on [Dexterity]-based skill checks, ranged attack rolls, initiative checks, and [Reflex] saving throws. The bonus also applies to your @ref{#armor-class,Armor Class}, your [Combat Maneuver Bonus] (if you are Tiny or smaller), and your [Combat Maneuver Defense].

@strong{[Constitution]}: Temporary increases to your [Constitution] score give you a bonus on your [Fortitude] saving throws. In addition, multiply your total Hit Dice by this bonus and add that amount to your current and total [hit points]. When the bonus ends, remove this total from your current and total [hit points].

@strong{[Intelligence]}: Temporary increases to your [Intelligence] score give you a bonus on [Intelligence]-based skill checks. This bonus also applies to any spell DCs based on [Intelligence].

@strong{[Wisdom]}: Temporary increases to your [Wisdom] score give you a bonus on [Wisdom]-based skill checks and [Will] saving throws. This bonus also applies to any spell DCs based on [Wisdom].

@strong{[Charisma]}: Temporary increases to your [Charisma] score give you a bonus on [Charisma]-based skill checks. This bonus also applies to any spell DCs based on [Charisma] and the DC to resist your channeled energy.

@strong{Permanent Bonuses}: Ability bonuses with a duration greater than 1 day actually increase the relevant ability score after 24 hours. Modify all skills and statistics related to that ability. This might cause you to gain skill points, [hit points], and other bonuses. These bonuses should be noted separately in case they are removed.
